. sort

  -to sorts file in alphabetical order
    calvin@localhost:~$ sort filename

  -if you want to sort in reverse alphabetical order
    calvin@localhost:~$ sort -r filename  
  -if you want to sort by field number
    calvin@localhost:~$ sort -k2 filename

. uniq
  -if there is a dublicate like, this command will not display it.
  Not: always sort then uniq
    calvin@localhost:~$ sort filename | uniq
  -give me the uniq but show me how many of the document we have, to see that you can run
    calvin@localhost:~$ sort file | uniq -c
  -only show repeated line 
    calvin@localhost:~$ sort file | uniq -d
